    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">06</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Sources and Historical Evidence</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyzing Texican Treaties and Government Records</h2><ul><li>Treaties formalized land grants and political agreements</li><li>Government records document legal status and administrative actions</li><li>These sources reveal official policies and settler responses</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Treaties and government documents provide structured evidence of Texican interactions with Mexican authorities, illustrating legal frameworks and political tensions [s13, s14]. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s14\">[14]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The 1824 Mexican Constitution influenced Texican rights and governance, as seen in official records.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Examine an excerpt from a land grant treaty and identify its implications for Texican settlers.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the legal language that shapes the meaning and impact of treaties.</p></div></div>",
