    "id": "slide52",
    "eyebrow": "Implications of Historical Gaps",
    "num": "16",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">16</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Implications of Historical Gaps</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">How Data Gaps Affect Texican Historical Understanding</h2><ul><li>Incomplete narratives risk oversimplifying Texican identity</li><li>Potential marginalization of minority voices within Texican society</li><li>Challenges in constructing accurate social, economic, and political histories</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The gaps in demographic, sociocultural, and economic data create challenges for historians, potentially leading to incomplete or biased interpretations of Texican history and identity. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Without full demographic data, the diversity within Texican communities may be underestimated, affecting cultural and political analyses.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss how acknowledging these gaps can improve historical research and interpretation.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring data limitations and presenting incomplete histories as definitive.</p></div></div>",
