    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">17</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Learner Reflection</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Identifying Missing Topics in Texican History</h2><ul><li>What questions remain unanswered about Texican demographics?</li><li>Which cultural aspects need further exploration?</li><li>Where are economic records insufficient or unclear?</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Learners are invited to reflect on and suggest topics or questions they feel are missing or unclear in the study of Texican history, promoting critical engagement with source limitations. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A learner might question how Texican women’s roles are documented or inquire about indigenous-Texican trade relations.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Contribute at least two questions or topics you believe require more research or clarity regarding Texican history.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Focusing only on well-documented topics and neglecting areas with sparse evidence.</p></div></div>",
