    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">18</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Review and Synthesis</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Consolidating Texican Identity and History</h2><ul><li>Texicans as a culturally diverse group with complex origins</li><li>Settlement shaped by legal, social, and geopolitical factors</li><li>Central role in Texas Revolution and early statehood</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This slide summarizes key points about Texican identity, culture, settlement, and historical roles, emphasizing the contested nature of some interpretations and the importance of source evaluation. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The transition from Texican to Texian to Texan reflects evolving political and cultural identities influenced by shifting sovereignties.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Summarize in your own words the main factors that defined Texican identity.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking the fluidity and contested nature of Texican identity over time.</p></div></div>",
