    "eyebrow": "Knowledge Check",
    "num": "19",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">19</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Knowledge Check</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Quiz: Texican Terminology and Identity</h2><ul><li>Distinguish between 'Texican,' 'Texian,' and 'Texan'</li><li>Identify key cultural influences on Texican identity</li><li>Recall major historical events involving Texicans</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This quiz assesses learners’ understanding of terminology, cultural background, and historical roles of Texicans, reinforcing key concepts and clarifying common confusions. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s3\">[3]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Question: Which term was primarily used during the Mexican period to describe settlers in Texas? Answer: Texican.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Complete the quiz questions to test your knowledge of Texican history and identity.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Confusing the terms or assuming they are interchangeable without historical context.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide55\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best defines the term &#39;Texican&#39; in its original historical context?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;A Spanish-speaking resident of Mexican Texas with cultural ties to Mexico&quot;,&quot;An Anglo-American settler who moved to Texas after 1836&quot;,&quot;A Native American tribe living in Texas&quot;,&quot;A term used exclusively for Texas politicians&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; originally referred to Spanish-speaking residents of Mexican Texas who had cultural and historical ties to Mexico, distinguishing them from Anglo settlers.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain how the settlement patterns and lifestyle of the Texicans were influenced by Mexican land grant policies and empresario contracts.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;A strong answer should describe the role of Mexican government land grants and empresario contracts in encouraging settlement, mention family and community life, and discuss frontier challenges faced by Texicans.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Mexican land grant policies and empresario contracts, such as those given to Stephen F. Austin, facilitated the settlement of Texicans by providing legal land ownership and encouraging families to establish communities. These policies shaped their lifestyle by promoting agriculture and ranching, while settlers faced challenges like conflicts with Native Americans and adapting to frontier conditions.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Mexican land grants and empresario contracts encouraged Texican settlement by providing land and legal rights&quot;,&quot;Settlement patterns were shaped by family-based communities and frontier challenges&quot;,&quot;Stephen F. Austin’s empresario contract was key in organizing Texican settlements&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
