    "num": "20",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">20</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Application Exercise</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyzing Primary Sources on Texicans</h2><ul><li>Examine excerpts from land grants, letters, or government records</li><li>Identify biases and limitations in the documents</li><li>Interpret the documents’ significance for Texican history</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Learners practice critical analysis of primary sources, applying skills to evaluate evidence about Texican settlement, culture, and political roles. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A land grant document may show legal ownership but omit details about indigenous displacement or settler conflicts.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze the provided document excerpt and answer: What does it reveal about Texican life? What might it omit or obscure?</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Accepting primary sources as fully objective without considering context or bias.</p></div></div>",
