    "eyebrow": "Transfer Practice",
    "num": "21",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">21</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Transfer Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Connecting Texican History to Broader Themes</h2><ul><li>Consider how identity evolves in multicultural frontier societies</li><li>Relate Texican experiences to other colonial and post-colonial contexts</li><li>Apply critical source evaluation to other historical case studies</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Learners extend their understanding by relating Texican history to wider historical and cultural processes, enhancing transfer of skills and knowledge. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Comparing Texican identity shifts with those of Cajuns in Louisiana or Métis in Canada highlights common patterns of cultural adaptation and political change.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify another historical group with a complex identity evolution and compare it to the Texicans.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texican history is unique without recognizing broader patterns.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide57\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best defines the term &#39;Texican&#39; in its original historical context?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;A Spanish-speaking resident of Mexican Texas with cultural ties to Mexico&quot;,&quot;An Anglo-American settler who moved to Texas after 1836&quot;,&quot;A Native American tribe living in Texas&quot;,&quot;A term used exclusively for Texas politicians&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; originally referred to Spanish-speaking residents of Mexican Texas who had cultural and historical ties to Mexico, distinguishing them from Anglo settlers.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain how the settlement patterns and lifestyle of the Texicans were influenced by Mexican land grant policies and empresario contracts.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;A strong answer should describe the role of Mexican government land grants and empresario contracts in encouraging settlement, mention family and community life, and discuss frontier challenges faced by Texicans.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Mexican land grant policies and empresario contracts, such as those given to Stephen F. Austin, facilitated the settlement of Texicans by providing legal land ownership and encouraging families to establish communities. These policies shaped their lifestyle by promoting agriculture and ranching, while settlers faced challenges like conflicts with Native Americans and adapting to frontier conditions.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Mexican land grants and empresario contracts encouraged Texican settlement by providing land and legal rights&quot;,&quot;Settlement patterns were shaped by family-based communities and frontier challenges&quot;,&quot;Stephen F. Austin’s empresario contract was key in organizing Texican settlements&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
